A man has been charged with possessing dozens of oven-ready partridges which were stolen from a meat lorry this week.

Sam James Tooke, 23, is accused of being involved in the disappearance of £6,500 worth of meat from delivery trucks in Spalding, Lincolnshire on Tuesday night and Wednesday morning.

Mr Tooke, of Whaplode, has been charged with possessing criminal property, namely 20 partridges.

